In this video, I present the changes made to the Colossus.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\loch
The Colossus\u8217\'92 attack is a horizontal line that naturally matches the formation of enemy units, which automatically line up next to each other when attacking. This attack design was originally introduced with the argument that it should reward micro-management and proper positioning. Unfortunately, positioning is usually automatically correct, and maps as well as classic unit compositions severely limit the room for creative positioning. As a result, it almost never happens that Colossi approach from a different direction than the main army. Since Colossi cannot defend themselves against air units, yet can be attacked by pure anti-air units, they are far too vulnerable to move around on their own. In practice, the idea of flexible positioning does not fit the reality of gameplay. It feels more like a punishment when a Colossus is not standing directly inside the main army to deal optimal damage \u8212\'97 for example, when a newly built Colossus reinforces from a different angle.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\loch
Even their cliff-walking ability is hardly usable, because, again, they are too vulnerable when alone \u8212\'97 especially against air units \u8212\'97 and there are too few units like Stalkers that can follow them over cliffs by using Blink. I don\u8217\'92t know for sure, but I could imagine that Blizzard\u8217\'92s original idea was that the Colossus should function on many maps like a combination of Shuttle and Reaver from StarCraft: Brood }{\loch
W}{\loch
ar \u8212\'97 except that the Colossus cannot move over water and thus has more limitations, giving players a reason to sometimes still use a Warp Prism for transportation. }
