\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\loch
Do you often see players having fun with Colossus positioning? Do you see many interesting positional plays against deathballs that show a clear difference between beginners and professional players? I simply don\u8217\'92t. Maybe most players just aren\u8217\'92t fast enough.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\loch
That is why the Colossus weapon is now again a continuous single-target attack, similar to a Sentry beam, but with automatic target locking and area-of-effect damage that also works against air units. The target lock ensures that the weapon has extended range as long as the Colossus continues attacking the same enemy unit. If the target or Colossus moves outside that extended range, the continuous beam breaks. This makes the Colossus flexible enough to operate alone on the map and hold its own against any unit type \u8212\'97 although there are still dedicated counters that can take it down efficiently.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\loch
Additionally, the new weapon deals damage while moving, which is useful both when chasing and when retreating \u8212\'97 and it makes micro with the Colossus genuinely enjoyable. You try to activate the attack, but immediately keep moving so the Colossus stays out of range of enemy units. The new danger posed by the Colossus also makes it an interesting harassment unit. Opponents need to hunt it down and can counter the attack effectively if they maintain proper spacing between units to avoid the splash damage.}
\par \pard\plain \s18\rtlch\af8\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af6\langfe2052{\loch
Overall, this creates more interesting micro on both sides and allows for more diverse unit compositions.}
